President Biden addressed a group of mayors at the White House and thanked them for their leadership and the work they do in their communities. He highlighted the importance of mayors in answering key questions that people have about their neighborhoods, safety, transportation, and the future of their towns. The President emphasized that mayors are the ones who get things done and have a direct impact on people's lives. He praised the mayors for their efforts in addressing the COVID-19 pandemic, revitalizing the economy, investing in infrastructure, fighting climate change, and improving public safety. He also discussed his administration's commitment to rebuilding the middle class, lowering costs for working families, and addressing issues such as gun safety, student debt relief, and lead pipe removal. President Biden expressed optimism about the future of the country and the ability to overcome challenges by working together.